    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Calories in Coffee with Milk: The Basics</h2>
            <p>The calorie count in coffee with milk depends on several factors, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Type of milk used</strong> (whole, skim, almond, soy, etc.)</li>
                <li><strong>Quantity of milk added</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Additives like sugar or sweeteners</strong></li>
            </ul>
            <p>On average:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Black coffee</strong>: 2-5 calories per cup (240 ml)</li>
                <li><strong>Coffee with a splash of whole milk</strong>: Approximately 20-30 calories</li>
                <li><strong>Coffee with skim milk</strong>: Around 10-15 calories</li>
                <li><strong>Coffee with almond milk (unsweetened)</strong>: About 5-10 calories</li>
                <li><strong>Coffee with soy milk (unsweetened)</strong>: Roughly 15-20 calories</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Detailed Breakdown: Milk Types and Their Impact</h2>
            <p><strong>Whole Milk:</strong> A tablespoon adds around 9 calories to your coffee. Half a cup adds about 75 calories.</p>
            <p><strong>Skim Milk:</strong> A lower-calorie option with about 5 calories per tablespoon or 40 calories per half cup.</p>
            <p><strong>Plant-Based Milks:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Almond Milk (Unsweetened):</strong> 5-7 calories per tablespoon or 30 calories per half cup.</li>
                <li><strong>Soy Milk (Unsweetened):</strong> 10-15 calories per tablespoon or 60 calories per half cup.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How Does Sugar Impact Calories?</h2>
            <p>Adding sugar increases calories. One teaspoon of sugar adds 16 calories, which can quickly increase your coffee’s calorie count.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Health Benefits of Coffee with Milk</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Rich in Calcium and Vitamin D:</strong> Milk provides essential nutrients for bone health.</li>
                <li><strong>Boosts Energy:</strong> The combination of caffeine and milk offers a balanced energy boost.</li>
                <li><strong>Enhanced Satiety:</strong> Milk in coffee can help curb hunger between meals.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Tips to Enjoy Low-Calorie Coffee with Milk</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Measure your milk portions to avoid overpouring.</li>
                <li>Opt for low-fat or plant-based options like skim milk or almond milk.</li>
                <li>Avoid added sugars; use natural sweeteners or enjoy it unsweetened.</li>
                <li>Enhance flavor with spices like cinnamon or nutmeg without adding calories.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

